<TEXT>
this media generalassociated press poll is 
based on telephone interviews april 29may 8 with 1204 adults in 
the continental united states the phone numbers were selected 
randomly by computer and interviews were conducted with the adult 
who had the most recent birthday 
the results were weighted to adjust for variations in the 
sample the poll has a 3point margin of error meaning the results 
theoretically would be within 3 points of the same 19 times out of 
20 if every adult american were asked the same questions the error 
margin is larger for subgroups 5 points for conservatives for 
example 
there are other sources of potential error in polls including 
the wording and order of questions these are the questions and 
responses in this poll 
1 the antiwar protests of the 1960s reached a peak in the 
summer of 1968 do you think the antiwar protests of the 1960s 
influenced us policy in vietnam 
yes 54 percent no 26 percent dont know or no answer 20 
percent 
1a if yes on question 1 do you think the antiwar protests 
prolonged us involvement in the vietnam war or shortened us 
involvement in the war 
prolonged 23 percent shortened 59 percent neither 9 
percent dont know or no answer 9 percent 
1b if yes on question 1 do you think the antiwar protests 
prevented the us from winning the war 
yes 30 percent no 58 percent dkna 12 percent 
2 do you think the antiwar protests of the 1960s have had a 
lasting effect on us foreign policy 
yes 57 percent no 27 percent dkna 16 percent 
2a if yes on question 2 overall do you think that effect has 
been positive or negative 
positive 47 percent negative 45 percent dkna 8 percent 
3 do you think the antiwar protests of the 1960s have had a 
lasting effect on american society 
yes 74 percent no 16 percent dkna 11 percent 
3a if yes to question 3 overall do you think that effect has 
been positive or negative 
positive 51 percent negative 41 percent dkna 8 percent 
4 compared to 20 years ago are you generally more liberal now 
more conservative or about the same 
liberal 17 percent conservative 29 percent same 37 percent 
does not apply 16 percent dkna 2 percent 
5 what about american society in general do you think it is 
more liberal now than it was 20 years ago more conservative or 
about the same 
liberal 52 percent conservative 28 percent same 15 percent 
dkna 6 percent 
6 please tell me if you agree or disagree with these statements 
a young people were more interested in changing society 20 
years ago than they are now agree 62 percent disagree 32 
percent dkna 6 percent 
b young people were more idealistic 20 years ago than they are 
now agree 65 percent disagree 29 percent dkna 7 percent 
c young people are more selfish now than they were 20 years 
ago agree 71 percent disagree 23 percent dkna 6 percent 
d young people are more apathetic now than they were 20 years 
ago agree 57 percent disagree 30 percent dkna 14 percent 
e young people are more realistic now than they were 20 years 
ago agree 54 percent disagree 36 percent dkna 11 percent 
</TEXT>
