<TEXT>
the supreme court today let stand a ruling 
that grants an exemption from state sales taxes to highstakes 
bingo games run by indian tribes 
the court without comment rejected an appeal by oklahoma 
officials seeking to impose the tax on revenue from a bingo game in 
tulsa run by the muscogee creek nation 
the justices in february 1987 ruled in a california case that 
state and local governments may not regulate highstakes bingo 
games and other gambling operations on indian reservations 
and last september the 10th us circuit court of appeals ruled 
that oklahoma could not force the muscogee creek nation to collect 
and remit the states 25 percent sales tax on the tribes bingo 
operations 
the appeals court said the states interest in collecting the 
tax is minimal in this case 
patrons do not travel onto creek lands to play bingo in order 
to avoid sales taxes the appeals court said creek nation 
bingo does not undermine the state economy or tax base the state 
is not losing tax revenues it would otherwise obtain from sales 
made outside of tribal boundaries 
the appeals court also based its ruling in part on the supreme 
courts ruling in the california case which said state and local 
governments have no say over indianrun gambling unless congress 
gives them permission 
the muscogee creek bingo game is conducted in tulsa on a 
100acre area known as the mackey site along the arkansas river 
the 10th circuit court said the land is indian territory in the 
same way any reservation belongs to native americans 
the appeals court also said the fact that the bingo game is 
managed by a nontribal entity indian country usa inc hired 
by the tribe does not alter the exempt status of the gambling 
operation 
forcing the tribe to collect and remit the sales tax would place 
a heavy burden on the indians even if the tax did not affect 
revenue for the creeks the appeals court said 
it added that the tribe would be subject to fines and liens on 
its property if it were held responsible for collecting the tax and 
then failed to do so 
asked for its views the reagan administration urged the court 
to reject oklahomas appeal 
the case is oklahoma tax commission vs muscogee creek nation 
871068 
</TEXT>
