a leading reformer said monday he doubts leon 
trotsky will be restored to communist party ranks even if the 
revolutionarys role in securing bolshevik power is recognized and 
his writings published 
asked by a greek reporter whether trotsky would be 
rehabilitated otto latsis deputy editor of the monthly kommunist 
said there are different kinds of rehabilitation 
trotsky may undergo what latsis termed civilian 
rehabilitation in that his contribution to the bolshevik 
revolution and to winning the civil war against the white guards 
should be recognized he said 
restoration to party ranks was another matter he said 
i dont think there is any basis for that said latsis 
trotsky was not excluded from the party in 1937 but in 1927 for 
his antiparty activity 
soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev announced in november that a 
central committee commission would review the cases of those who 
had suffered under dictator josef v stalin and would restore honor 
to people who were unjustly repressed 
since then revolutionaries nikolai v bukharin lev kamenev and 
grigory zinoviev are among those who have been formally cleared of 
what are now seen as trumpedup charges in show trials in the late 
1930s but they have not been restored to party ranks 
leading historian yuri n afanasyev said on june 17 that trotsky 
should be exonerated of criminal charges and his works republished 
for all 
trotsky has been reviled for half a century as a traitor and the 
archenemy of socialism 
recognition of his revolutionary role would directly counter an 
orthodoxy that has gone unchallenged for 60 years it would also 
signal how deeply the soviet union is now questioning the legacy of 
stalin who ruled the country from 1924 to his death in 1953 
born lev d bronstein the son of a jewish farmer trotsky was a 
central figure in the 1917 bolshevik revolution and the architect 
of the red armys victory in the civil war that followed it 
he served successively as commissar for foreign affairs and then 
for war but was bested by stalin in the infighting which followed 
the death of vladimir i lenin in 1924 
after his expulsion from the party in 1927 trotsky was expelled 
from the country in 1929 in the 193638 show trials that 
accompanied stalins bloody purges trotsky was accused of treason 
in 1940 he was murdered in mexico city reportedly by a soviet 
agent 
talking about rehabilitation for trotsky latsis said we have 
to stop the atmosphere around trotsky he played an important role 
in the civil war and the revolution we have to look at the role he 
played not more not less not better not worse 
his books should be available latsis added they are 
historical documents and a contribution to the general struggle 
soviet people should know about them 
afanasyev said on june 17 that all those accused on false 
evidence should be rehabilitated including trotsky 
