the airbus 320 has had two serious electrical problems since april 
the first on the inaugural flight march 26 and the second june 23 
on a flight that was to have gone to amsterdam but did not depart 
the aircraft carries 168 people and consumes 40 percent less 
fuel than similar two or three engine jets 
it is the first civilian airliner equipped with a fully 
computerized flightcontrol system which the manufacturer says 
permits safer electronically controlled flight 
instead of the old control column in front of the pilot there 
is a pistolgrip side stick linked to five computers that 
modify and relay the pilots directions to wing and tail flaps 
in the event of total failure of the electrical flight control 
system and all computers the jet is equipped with a mechanical 
cable link to the tail that would allow the pilot to fly manually 
although with reduced maneuverablity 
the plane operates with a twoman flight crew earlier this 
year pilots and flight engineers of frances largest domestic 
carrier air inter called a series of protest strikes saying 
three crewmembers were needed for safety 
newspapers quoted romain kroes a union spokesman as saying 
sundays accident proved the necessity for a third person in the 
cockpit he said a flight engineer is needed to take over manual 
controls in case of failure of the electronic system of supplying 
the planes engines with fuel 
