<TEXT>
the house on monday approved legislation to 
grant some school districts a deadline extension for drawing up 
plans to get deadly asbestos out of their school buildings 
the bill was sent by voice vote to the senate where a similar 
proposal is pending 
under a 1986 law school districts have until next oct 12 to 
survey their facilities for the presence of friable or crumbling 
asbestos and to draft plans to get the cancercausing material 
safely removed or stabilized 
the house bill would allow a governor to extend this deadline to 
may 9 1989 the legislation would not change the july 9 1989 
date by which the 1986 law requires school districts to begin 
implementing their plans 
congress is in the process of allowing casebycase deadline 
extensions because school officials around the country have 
complained that a shortage of trained personnel and money are 
hampering the drafting of plans 
the environmental protection agency has estimated that as many 
as 30000 schools may contain dangerous asbestos whose fibers have 
been proven to cause lung cancer and other respiratory ailments 
