<TEXT>
syrianallied palestinian dissidents 
overran beiruts chatilla refugee camp in a 13hour battle monday 
and plo chairman yasser arafats fighters surrendered or laid down 
their weapons police said 
the fall of the camp dealt a serious setback for arafats 
mainstream fatah which has been fighting col saeed mousas 
radical fatahuprising faction since may 1 for control of the 
chatilla and nearby bourj elbarajneh camps 
the palestine liberation organization openly blamed syria for 
the fighting 
the plo executive committee the guerrilla movements 
policymaking body said the government of syrian president hafez 
assad is implementing a black political scheme aimed at 
undermining the palestinian presence in lebanon 
about 140 of arafats men in chatilla surrendered to syrian and 
libyan officers police said 
sixty other arafat loyalists including 45 believed to be 
wounded told libyan mediators they had put down their weapons and 
