the occasion this single fact assured me about glasnost much 
more than speeches made by soviet officials he says a few 
years ago such a visit of a leading soviet composer and playing by 
a jewish immigrant was unimaginable now it is real i hope such a 
normal attitude will go forward 
in addition to his concerts feltsman is cutting records and 
talking about a special school for budding american pianists he 
has made two recordings already and soon will make two more 
i think recording is one of the most important parts of the 
life of a musician he says the performing artist plays and 
it is disappearing in air now im already thinking not about 
success but about leaving some legacy 
part of that legacy too could be a special program for 
promising young american pianists of those hes worked with he 
says their main trouble even for the best i heard is their 
training at a very early age if you miss something at 6 7 8 or 
9 technically physically psychologically you will never get it 
back later 
feltsman has talked with some wealthy people about endowing a 
school free but available only to the most gifted 
with such things as music if you want to get good results you 
have to be very tough at the beginning he says and the 
principle has to be talent not ability to pay you cannot buy a 
musical gift with money 
asked whether hell be nervous about the mostly mozart opening 
and televised concert feltsman says i am very nervous always 
probably thats the way you have to pay for the joy to play 
the music 
