britains merchandise trade deficit soared to a 
record 1705 billion pounds or 29 billion in may with imports 
running at their highest level since last summer the government 
reported monday 
the pound fell sharply on the news losing about 1 cent against 
the dollar to stand at 17043 share prices on the london stock 
exchange also took a beating 
the seasonally adjusted trade deficit compared with a revised 
deficit of 123 billion pounds or 209 billion in april and a 
deficit of 106 billion pounds or 18 billion in may 1987 the 
department of trade and industry said 
analysts forecasts for the merchandise trade gap had ranged 
from 900 million or 15 billion dollars to 12 billion pounds 
or 204 billion 
meanwhile britains current account shortfall in may which 
includes invisible trade such as services overseas investment 
earnings and official transfer payments widened to a record 1205 
billion pounds or 205 billion that compared with a revised 
deficit of 728 million pounds or 124 billion in april and a 
deficit of 361 million pounds or 614 million in may 1987 
market forecasts for the may current account deficit rangd from 
450 million pounds or 765 million to 800 million pounds or 
136 billion 
news of the widerthanexpected deficits pushed the pound down 
against both the us dollar and the west german deutsche mark 
despite expectations that a further fall in the pound might prompt 
